The paper deals with the experimental study of algorithms for online bipartite matching, which is a problem in computer science related to data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). The study involves evaluating the performance of different algorithms on random inputs and real-life instances, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the worst-case and average-case performance of the algorithms, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
